PrecisEnactment of the PROGRAMMING UNDERTAKING REGULATIONS which, for the purposes of the Copyright Act, define "programming undertaking" as a network that consists of a programming originator (one who directly or indirectly transmits its audio and video programs by telecommunication to a distributor) and a programming distributor (one who transmits the programs to the public), EFFECTIVE August 31, 1993.
